00:02:24.943 --> 00:02:30.043
It did not take long for rumours of witchcraft to spread around Salem

00:02:30.383 --> 00:02:35.433
and villagers would accuse each other of using magic to harm one another.

00:02:36.843 --> 00:02:40.343
Soon enough, the trials and executions started.

00:02:41.183 --> 00:02:48.073
The first to be executed was a lady called Bridget Bishop, after it was decided that it was she

00:02:48.263 --> 00:02:53.973
who had cursed the two young girls and had also attacked various other members of the community.

00:02:55.223 --> 00:03:00.663
As the trials continued, the two young girls began to make other accusations.

00:03:01.103 --> 00:03:05.213
Fingers were pointed and suspicions continued to grow.

00:03:06.233 --> 00:03:14.383
This cycle continued until hundreds had been accused, imprisoned, tortured and in some cases killed.

00:03:15.773 --> 00:03:20.963
20 of the accused, 14 of which were women, would face death by hanging.

00:03:22.143 --> 00:03:27.253
One, an 81-year-old man called Giles Corey, who was accused of

00:03:27.253 --> 00:03:31.403
witchcraft along with his wife, would escape the hangman’s noose.

00:03:32.303 --> 00:03:36.253
I’m afraid though hanging would have been a blessing for Corey.

00:03:36.503 --> 00:03:38.953
He was to suffer something much worse.

